BASICS
======

INTEGER LITERALS: [{+|-} digits [radix]
> radix = h, q/o, d, b, r, t (decimal alt), y (binary alt)
> literalx beginning with letters must start with a 0 (e.g. 0A1h instead of A1h)

CONSTANT INTEGER EXPRESSIONS (32bit)
> operators (order): ( ), {+|-} (unary), {*|/}, MOD, {+|-} (add,subtract)

REAL NUMBER LITERALS: [sign]integer.[integer] [exponent]
> sign: {+|-}
> exponent: E[{+|-}]integer

CHARACTER LITERALS
> must be enclosed in single or double quoutes

RESERVED WORDS: instr mnemonics, reg names, directives (e.g. .data .code), attributes, operators, predefined symbols (e.g. @data)

INSTRUCTIONS: [label: ] mnemonic [operands] [;comment]

OPERANDS: can be registers, memory, integer expression, i/o port